name: Vishal's Goan Food,

reviews.review_text: This is a hidden gem in Candolim, in a lane off the main road. We were bored of all the restaurants which had live singing or karaoke and had just touristy vibes. Happened to find this place on Google and decided to visit it with friends. The food here is awesome, prepared fresh by the owner and chef Vishal who checks on his guests personally for preferences and taste. He will not hesitate to cook up something not on the menu too. We tried the Pomfret, Surmai and Veg thalis which were delicious. The thalis are available only from 12.30 to 3.30pm. The butter garlic prawns were also very good. Also had rava fried chonak and was hooked to the delicate fried coating and freshness of the fish. We ended up eating 3 times in the 2 days we were there. You definitely should eat here, you will not be disappointed. Thanks to Vishal for being a great host, you can taste the passion for cooking in his food. Good luck to you Vishal,  just dont convert this great place to a karaoke bar!!

This is hands down one of the best seafood restaurants I’ve ever been to!
I tried a variety of dishes, and each one was cooked to perfection—fresh, flavorful, and beautifully presented.
The quality of the seafood truly stood out.

The service was friendly and attentive, adding to the overall great atmosphere of the place.
It’s definitely a must-visit in goa for seafood lovers.
I can’t recommend this place enough!

Good place for thali meals. Bit expensive when compared to regular meal options. But really nice service and yummy food. Prawn curry was yummy. Also the kingfish fry and prawn fry in rava. Must try item.But Food is not spicy, you will be disappointed if you love spicy food. It's really amazing to see the owner 'Vishal' was handing over the food for each and every customer personally and was talking with them atleast for 5 min. That really feels like we are a guest at his home. Do try when you are in Goa.

description:
**Vishal's Goan Food: A Culinary Treasure in Candolim**

Tucked away from the bustling main streets of Candolim, **Vishal's Goan Food** earns an impressive rating of **4.6** from **671 reviewers**, making it a cherished find for locals and visitors alike. The restaurant shines as a beacon of **Goan cuisine**, particularly known for its **thalis**, **butter garlic prawns**, and the much-raved about **ros omelette**. With 70 mentions of thali across reviews, it's clear that this traditional meal is a highlight not to be missed.

**Ambiance & Design**

Stepping into Vishal's Goan Food, you are greeted by an inviting ambiance that balances warmth and charm. The interior is adorned with traditional Goan decor, featuring vibrant table settings and local artifacts that resonate with the region's rich culture. Warm lighting casts a cozy glow over each table, while soft background music gently enhances the dining experience without overpowering conversation. Customer photos reveal a quaint yet lively atmosphere where you can savor your meal away from the touristy chaos.

![Delicious Thali](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/geougc-cs/AHRlGdkL7HoL4XfN79GFLATFn6IbTy2HnrDp9p-qqDTR2Lx6jGCPvZUc8n7pvgbGyIazzZmHXAfa_iIT7HpL3srpPQdWHN2OwDBoiesEEkEJUnrIh3rbNteTpAwGEx9fs-LWclxpLlgv-Q=w375-h563-p)

**Menu & Culinary Experience**

The menu at Vishal's is a love letter to Goan culinary traditions, with fresh seafood playing a starring role. Diners rave about the **Surmai** and **Pomfret**, elegantly presented on colorful platters that make the meal visually appealing. The **thali meals**, served between **12:30 PM and 3:30 PM**, are a must-try, offering a sampling of authentic flavors at an attractive price, even if some find them a bit pricier than average. The **butter garlic prawns** and **rava fried chonak** have garnered special mention for their light, crispy textures and rich flavors, showcasing the restaurant's commitment to freshness and quality.

![Fresh Seafood](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/geougc-cs/AHRlGdmjrzM6w2iQxjte5K_EbMM5RctZT6iOxZ5j87KMfj5g7IGK1lW9ZtXM2j96IaCNiZ2Ib-YPD12yJ4dC-SxtSYEaVkRIh_CxiKv0RHoigMS9ghvgDvdE5e9Vhl07-i0C58EnrPq2zA=w375-h281-p)

**Customer Experience & Service**

What truly sets Vishal's Goan Food apart is the exemplary service led by owner and chef Vishal himself. Guests report feeling like cherished friends rather than mere customers, as Vishal often personally attends to everyone, making recommendations and ensuring each dish meets individual preferences. The friendly and attentive staff further enhances the dining experience, making each visit feel special. It's also worth noting from the reviews that while the flavors are carefully balanced, those looking for spicier dishes may find the seasoning milder than expected.

**Popularity & Reviews**

Feedback from patrons is overwhelmingly positive, with many calling it one of the best seafood restaurants in Goa. The restaurant has gained traction on social media platforms, with diners eagerly sharing their experiences and photos. This enthusiasm suggests that word of mouth and social media buzz will only continue to elevate its status amongst food lovers in the region.

![Vishal's Warm Welcome](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/geougc-cs/AHRlGdn7-jOIhxb3O0hBgVIa2dRoQR6ySWBOjWqgZekxSSmE6hYMVOqmmcJfc6_8pw-5E2WLuQJgkkY6qrBi3M2PRP3DbzeFfcpt49q8pBJiN8X5kPfPn1nA3aM9w05QDR3Jvxj7mDM=w375-h281-p)

**Conclusion**

Vishal's Goan Food is a delightful escape from ordinary dining. With its flavorful dishes, welcoming ambiance, and personal touch from Chef Vishal, it promises a memorable culinary adventure in the heart of Candolim. It is undoubtedly a must-visit destination for anyone seeking authentic Goan cuisine, and as one reviewer aptly put it, "You will not be disappointed."
